snippet.textDisplay: I cant help but feel a whirlwind of emotions watching this as a daughter of a loving father who has three daughters. As much as 'wanwun' fills me with immense pride  as it is the representation of our rich heritage and values we hold dear, it disheartens me realising the fact that how the mixed culture nowadays has turned beautiful occasions as marriage into something that adds on a father's concerns. I hope we embrace the  wisdom of our ancestors and strive for the marriages that are grounded in love rather than excessive expenses.
